Nine years later, the mountain of 30 million euros has sprung up.
The building is part of a revitalization project also includes underground parking, a supermarket, a post office, a few buildings and townhouses for a total of 50 homes.
In early November, the mountain of books received the second prize "Best Library of NL 2012."
Moreover, the project has been selected for the Dutch National Wood Award 2012.
Thus, this small town dull, which until now had nothing more to offer than a post-modern pedestrian zone and a town hall of a staggering ugliness, whose white facades suggest they support a dairy, was enriched by a contemporary architectural work.
The most important thing is that Spijkenisse now has the first public cultural edifice in its history.
The long road to reading
First impression: Eldorado book under bell to cheese.
Certainly, a lift takes you through the heart of the massif, but the real joy of reading and architecture are open to you when you stroll through the floor of the building to the discovery of its topography.
