Even the architects and engineers of the building hardened do not want unknown materials.
"We wanted to work with recycled materials," says Joop Trouborst, leader of the project to the municipality of Spijkenisse, in a response to the Standard.
Thus, one day we found in a Frisian farm ad hoc waste from agriculture.
In the Netherlands, has been used for years in the synthetic membrane of a millimetre thick as substrate in greenhouses and fields.
It is cheap and it saves time.
The thin membrane is used for one or two seasons, then we can throw it.
For the library, the membrane was compressed, for the first time in such quantities, thick plates of four centimeters.
Under the influence of heat and pressure, "Landbouwplastic" (KPL) changes color and turns into a dark material, homogeneous and resistant, the smell evokes both a new car and sports footwear.
